abstract: Gunmen attack security forces headquarters in Benghazi, Libya, killing nine people and wounding 24; government blames Islamic extremist group Ansar al-Shariah for attack.
lead_paragraph: Gunmen attacked a security forces headquarters in Libya’s eastern city of Benghazi early Friday, killing nine people and wounding 24, the authorities said. The government blamed Ansar al-Shariah, an Islamic extremist group accused of being behind the attack on an American diplomatic post in Benghazi.
